  "local_port": 45892,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Account opening in Zerodha states 48 hours, I have submitted all documents and it has been 10 days with no luck. Pathetic support, how to escalate?",
  "response": "If you've been waiting for more than the stated 48 hours for your account to be opened with Zerodha and have received inadequate support, you can take the following steps to escalate the issue:\n\n1. **Contact Customer Support Again**: Sometimes issues can be resolved by giving customer support another chance. Reach out via phone, email, or live chat.\n\n2. **Email a Formal Complaint**: Draft a detailed email explaining your issue, the timeline, and any previous communications you've had with customer support. Send this email to support@zerodha.com or complaints@zerodha.com.\n\n3. **Use Social Media**: Companies often respond quickly to issues raised on social media platforms. Post your issue on platforms like Twitter or Facebook and tag Zerodha's official accounts.\n\n4. **SEBI Complaint Portal**: If your issue is still not resolved, you can escalate it to the Securities and Exchange Board of India (SEBI) through their complaint portal, SCORES (https://scores.gov.in).\n\n5. **Contact the Nodal Officer**: Zerodha has a designated Nodal Officer for handling escalations. You can email the Nodal Officer at nodalofficer@zerodha.com.\n\n6. **Visit a Local Branch**: If there is a Zerodha branch nearby, visit them in person to address your issue.\n\nHere\u2019s a sample email you can use to escalate your issue:\n\n---\n\nSubject: Escalation of Account Opening Delay \u2013 [Your Name]\n\nDear Zerodha Team,\n\nI am writing to express my dissatisfaction with the account opening process. I submitted all the required documents for my account opening on [date], but despite the stated 48-hour processing time, it has been [number] days with no resolution.\n\nI have reached out to customer support multiple times, but my issue remains unresolved. This delay is causing significant inconvenience.\n\nPlease escalate this matter to the concerned department and expedite the process. I expect prompt action on this matter.\n\nThank you,\n[Your Name]\n[Your Contact Information]\n[Your Client ID (if available)]\n\n---\n\nTaking these steps should help in getting your issue resolved more quickly.",
